It should be noted, moreover, that the number of the regions was, from the outset, not only equal to that of the deacons and subdeacons‚ but that it also evidently affected that of the acolytes‚ of whom there were forty-two‚ that 15, six to each region. If we add to these the subdeacon, we have in each region seven clerics under the rank of deacon‚ namely, the six acolytes and the subdeacon‚ who was a kind of head acolyte.
